I'm having no luck in trying to build an SCR model using the usual trick of
tying a pair of NPN/PNP transistors together.  Here's the info.  Can you
suggest solutions?  There are three problems -- one that shows in the
documented run, the others noted by comments in the CMD file.  Thanks.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------


scr.cmd:

transient 1.0e-2
wave power gnd sin amp=10 freq=60
***** ACTUALLY want amp=170, but even untriggered case bombs *****
wave trig gnd pie {0,0, 4e-3,0, 4.1e-3,1, 4.323e-3,1, 4.333e-3,0, 8.333,0}
***** ACTUALLY want to use wave ... bit{...}, but delay=4e-3 doesn't work *****
plot {v(power), v(trig), i(rload, power)}

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

scr.fa:

.model nbjt npn
.model pbjt pnp

.subckt scr a k g
r0 n0 a 1e3
q1 g n0 a ss1 pbjt
q2 n0 g k ss2 nbjt
.ends scr

xcr1 anode gnd gate scr
rload anode power 10
rtrig gate trig 100

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

